Here's the result of running `cat -n` on /workspace/solution.py:
     1	n, m = map(int, input().split())
     2	
     3	products = []
     4	for i in range(n):
     5	    line = list(map(int, input().split()))
     6	    price = line[0]
     7	    count = line[1]
     8	    functions = set(line[2:2+count])
     9	    products.append((price, functions))
    10	
    11	# Check if there exists a pair (i, j) where i is strictly superior to j
    12	found = False
    13	
    14	for i in range(n):
    15	    if found:
    16	        break
    17	    for j in range(n):
    18	        if i == j:
    19	            continue
    20	
    21	        price_i, functions_i = products[i]
    22	        price_j, functions_j = products[j]
    23	
    24	        # Check condition 1: P_i >= P_j
    25	        if price_i < price_j:
    26	            continue
    27	
    28	        # Check condition 2: j-th product has all functions of i-th product
    29	        if not functions_i.issubset(functions_j):
    30	            continue
    31	
    32	        # Check condition 3: P_i > P_j OR j-th product has functions i doesn't have
    33	        if price_i > price_j or len(functions_j - functions_i) > 0:
    34	            found = True
    35	            break
    36	
    37	print("Yes" if found else "No")
